<p><sup>1</sup> Winner of the <a href="/wiki/Nebula_Award_for_Best_Novel" title="Nebula Award for Best Novel">Nebula Award for Best Novel</a></p>
<p><a name="Retro_Hugos" id="Retro_Hugos"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Hugo_Award_for_Best_Novel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Retro Hugos">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Retro Hugos</span></h3>
<p>Retro Hugos were awarded 50 years after years in which <a href="/wiki/World_Science_Fiction_Convention" title="World Science Fiction Convention" class="mw-redirect">World Conventions</a> didn't give awards — <i>note: no "Best Novel" Hugo was awarded at the 1957 convention, but Hugos were awarded in other categories, hence there was no "Retro Hugo" for 1957 awarded in 2007</i>.</p>
<table class="wikitable">
<tr>
<th>Year<br />
(awarded)</th>
<th>Winner</th>
<th>Other nominees</th>
</tr>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;">
<th>1954
<p>(2004)</p>
</th>
<td><i><a href="/wiki/Fahrenheit_451" title="Fahrenheit 451">Fahrenheit 451</a></i><br />
by <a href="/wiki/Ray_Bradbury" title="Ray Bradbury">Ray Bradbury</a></td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>2 <i><a href="/wiki/Childhood%27s_End" title="Childhood's End">Childhood's End</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Arthur_C._Clarke" title="Arthur C. Clarke">Arthur C. Clarke</a></li>
<li>3 <i><a href="/wiki/Mission_of_Gravity" title="Mission of Gravity">Mission of Gravity</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Hal_Clement" title="Hal Clement">Hal Clement</a></li>
<li>4 <i><a href="/wiki/The_Caves_of_Steel" title="The Caves of Steel">The Caves of Steel</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Isaac_Asimov" title="Isaac Asimov">Isaac Asimov</a></li>
<li>5 <i><a href="/wiki/More_Than_Human" title="More Than Human">More Than Human</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Theodore_Sturgeon" title="Theodore Sturgeon">Theodore Sturgeon</a></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;">
<th>1951
<p>(2001)</p>
</th>
<td><i><a href="/wiki/Farmer_in_the_Sky" title="Farmer in the Sky">Farmer in the Sky</a></i><br />
by <a href="/wiki/Robert_A._Heinlein" title="Robert A. Heinlein">Robert A. Heinlein</a></td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>2 <i><a href="/wiki/Pebble_in_the_Sky" title="Pebble in the Sky">Pebble in the Sky</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Isaac_Asimov" title="Isaac Asimov">Isaac Asimov</a></li>
<li>3 <i><a href="/wiki/The_Lion,_the_Witch_and_the_Wardrobe" title="The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe">The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/C._S._Lewis" title="C. S. Lewis">C. S. Lewis</a></li>
<li>4 <i><a href="/wiki/Lensman" title="Lensman" class="mw-redirect">First Lensman</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/E._E._Smith" title="E. E. Smith">Edward E. Smith, Ph.D.</a></li>
<li>5 <i><a href="/wiki/The_Dying_Earth" title="The Dying Earth">The Dying Earth</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Jack_Vance" title="Jack Vance">Jack Vance</a></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;">
<th>1946
<p>(1996)</p>
</th>
<td><i><a href="/wiki/Foundation_and_Empire" title="Foundation and Empire">The Mule</a></i><br />
by <a href="/wiki/Isaac_Asimov" title="Isaac Asimov">Isaac Asimov</a><br />
(republished as Part II of <i><a href="/wiki/Foundation_and_Empire" title="Foundation and Empire">Foundation and Empire</a></i>)</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>2 <i><a href="/wiki/The_World_of_Null-A" title="The World of Null-A">The World of Null-A</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/A._E._van_Vogt" title="A. E. van Vogt">A. E. van Vogt</a></li>
<li>3 <i><a href="/wiki/That_Hideous_Strength" title="That Hideous Strength">That Hideous Strength</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/C._S._Lewis" title="C. S. Lewis">C. S. Lewis</a></li>
<li>4 <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Destiny_Times_Three&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Destiny Times Three (page does not exist)">Destiny Times Three</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Fritz_Leiber" title="Fritz Leiber">Fritz Leiber</a></li>
<li>5 <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Red_Sun_of_Danger&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Red Sun of Danger (page does not exist)">Red Sun of Danger</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Edmond_Hamilton" title="Edmond Hamilton">Edmond Hamilton</a> (writing as Brett Sterling)</li>
</ul>
